A little snippet from our conversation! Thank you so much to @RakeemOmar for having me on @bbcwm, it was an absolute joy taking to you 🙌🏽. Hilarious hearing how positive I feel about turning 30 now given how much I was panicking in the months leading up to it 😅 https://t.co/51ucDmaDey
@staceycav It really is! But even then, I felt silly for not sticking to 9-5 so I’d try and force myself… then get frustrated with myself for being unproductive 🤦🏽‍♀️
@staceycav Exactly! It’s crazy how much faster and more efficiently you work during hours that work for you 🙌🏽
@leahtaylor @ellaluciewrites Here’s to us night owls 😅🥂

@ellaluciewrites It really is a nightmare because you either end up forcing work out that may not be your best, or working later because you just couldn’t focus! Yep 12-8 are my golden hours, too 😂 I can get so much done with far less faffing.

Not all of us are wired for 9-5 or early mornings. There’s no shame in that! 

Everyone works differently and it’s far better to work hours where you’re actually productive, rather than starting at a screen blankly for ages for the first part of the day.

If you’re a freelancer/someone who’s lucky enough to work in a company that offers flexible hours, I cannot stress this enough:

Work hours that work for YOU! 🙌🏽 

It’s taken me far too long to suss this out, but better late than never because I’ve never been more productive 😅
